The paper deals with logic programming, program correctness, completeness, and declarative programming, which are all topics that fall under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of a SAT solver and pruning techniques also suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of delays in Prolog, which is a feature of programming languages and falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL). The focus on correctness and completeness suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE), and the use of proof methods and declarative diagnosis suggests a connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
